sAuthor: Gomes, R. d. S.[Rossimar dos Santos]
Citation.sAbstract: Liquid-liquid equilibrium (LLE) data for systems involving 1-butanol + water + protic ionic liquids ethyl-2-hydroxyethylammonium propionate [E2HEA][Pr], diethylammonium propionate [DEA]]Pr], or butylammonium propionate [BA][Pr] were determined at 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure. The solubility curves were obtained by the cloud point method and correlated with different empirical equations. The compositions of the phases in equilibrium were determined based on the fitting equation of the binodal curve and the lever rule. Data quality was verified using the semi-empirical methods by Othmer-Tobias and Hand. The liquid-liquid equilibrium data was correlated using the non-random two liquid model (NRTL) and UNIversal QUAsi Chemical (UNIQUAC) model and good fit was found between the correlations and the experimental data, yielding overall root-meansquare deviations of 1.56% for NRTL and 1.78% for UNIQUAC.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid-Liquid Equilibria Data of Protic Ionic Liquid (Ethyl-2-hydroxyethylammonium Propionate, Diethylammonium Propionate, or Butylammonium Propionate) with 1-Butanol + Water at 298.15 K
